FOUR dangerous awaiting-trial prisoners escaped on Sunday from holding cells in Hoedspruit, outside Phalaborwa. Provincial cops spokesman Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the men, aged between 31 and 41, escaped through the roof. Jacky Sekgobela (41) from Botswana Village, outside Tzaneen, was arrested for house and business robberies. Sekgobela is accused of committing several crimes in Limpopo and Mpumalanga and is regarded as dangerous. Dyayani Baloyi (39), believed to be from Tzaneen, is facing charges of murder, rape, house robbery and business robbery and is also considered dangerous. Pompi Khosa (36) from Cottondale in Acornhoek was bust for housebreaking and theft. The fourth suspect, Wilson Letebele (31) from Willows Village outside Hoedspruit, is facing charges of house robbery and housebreaking. Charges of escaping from lawful custody were opened. “We’re requesting anyone with information that can lead to the rearrest of these criminals to contact the station commander of Hoedspruit Colonel Rhulani Mabasa on 082 565 8253, or Captain Cobra Moriri at 082 573 4773,” said Mojapelo.